Package: loopmonitor
Title: On-Demand Status Queries and Loop Control for Long-Running R Programs
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Haim", "Bar", email = "haim.bar@uconn.edu",
    role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Provides ipc_for(), ipc_while(), and ipc_repeat() as drop-in
    replacements for R's loop constructs, enabling on-demand inspection and
    control of long-running loops from a second terminal using the ipc
    command-line tool (from the companion Python package).  Status, tracked
    values, and ETA are written to a JSON state file after every iteration;
    commands (peek, plot, continue, break, set, checkpoint, stack, memory)
    are delivered via a polled command file without requiring signal handlers.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Imports: jsonlite
Encoding: UTF-8
RoxygenNote: 7.3.1
